              },
              "free_text": [
                " Pd-300 neutron generator"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "About 7 gram of high purity Sc2O3 powder(natural",
                "isotopic composition) was pressed at 10 ton/cm2, and",
                "a pellet, 0.4 cm thick and 2.0 cm in diameter was",
                "obtained. Monitor foils (Nb, 99.99% pure, 0.5 mm",
                "thick) of the same diameter as the pellets were then",
                "attached in front and at the back of each sample."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The crystal geometry is 70.1 x 72.3 mm in",
                "diameter and length. The relative efficiency is about",
                "68%, and energy resolution is 1.69 keV at 1332 keV",
                "gamma ray from Co-60. The efficiency of the detector",
                "was pre-calibrated using various standard gamma",
                "sources, which were Mn-54, Co-57, Co-60, Cd-109,",
                "Ba-133, Cs-137, Eu-152, Am-241 and Ra-226."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "FISCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The neutron flux was monitored by a uranium",
                "fission chamber."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Irradiation of the samples was lasted about 2",
                "hours with a yield around 3E10 to 4E10 n/s. The groups",
                "of samples were placed at 0deg., 90deg. or 135deg.",
                "angles relative to the beam direction and centered",
                "about the T-Ti target at distances of around 5 cm."
              ]
            }
          ],
